{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: medicationstatement-eu-core_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates FSH instances for a patient's medication record conforming to
    the EU Core profiles. The template operates in one of two modes selected
    by a top-level branch on whether `medication` is empty:

      MODE A — No known medications:
        A single MedicationStatement instance is emitted carrying the SNOMED
        "No known medications" code. One HTML cell is produced. No Medication
        instance is generated.

      MODE B — Medication present:
        TWO FSH instances are emitted in sequence:
          1. Medication (MedicationEuCore)      — the drug itself
          2. MedicationStatement (MedicationStatementEuCore) — the statement
             linking patient, drug, dosage, and reason

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    Mode A  MedicationStatement : MedicationStatementEuCore
    Mode B  Medication          : MedicationEuCore
            MedicationStatement : MedicationStatementEuCore

  TOP-LEVEL BRANCH PATTERN
    The entire %%FSH%% body is wrapped in a single top-level `{% if medication
    is empty %} … {% else %} … {% endif %}`. This is the most prominent use
    of the "template-level conditional" pattern in the project — the number
    and type of instances emitted depends entirely on whether the caller
    supplies medication data.

  MODE A — NO KNOWN MEDICATIONS
    - Single MedicationStatement registered via setInstance().
    - medicationCodeableConcept = $sct#787481004 "No known medications"
    - effectivePeriod carries a data-absent-reason extension (no dates known).
    - One HTML cell "No known medications" (no HEAD, no table structure).
    - CSS class: hl7__ips first25 (narrow first column).

  MODE B — MEDICATION INSTANCE (first)
    Medication coding — mutually exclusive priority:
      1. SNOMED CT (`medication.code.code`) — used when present.
      2. RxNorm (`medication.rxnorm`) — used only when SNOMED is absent.
    `code.text[=]` — when a preferredTerm exists, it is set on the code using
      the [=] operator. Note: `[=]` on a non-repeating element like `.text`
      is unconventional; SUSHI resolves this as addressing the last-opened
      coding context. Callers should verify SUSHI compilation output.
    `formdisplay` local variable — captures the manufactured dose form display
      text (prefixed with ", ") for reuse in both the Medication text.div and
      MedicationStatement HTML td 3. Empty string when no form is present.
    `activeIngredient` — ingredient[0] with isActive = true; conditional.

  MODE B — MEDICATION STATEMENT (second)
    Five-column HTML table: Medication | Since | Form | Dosage | Reason

    medicationReference — links to the Medication instance above by UUID.

    TD 1 — Medication name with optional "as needed" suffix:
      `medication.asNeeded` may be:
        - "true" (string) → appends " - as needed" to the display name and
          emits `dosage[+].asNeededBoolean = true`
        - a CodeableConcept object (`.display`, `.system`, `.code`) → appends
          " - <display>" and emits `dosage[+].asNeededCodeableConcept`

    TD 4 — AI-generated dosage injection:
      `medication.dosagefsh` is a pre-formatted FSH dosage string produced by
      an AI system and injected using `| raw`. The `contdose` variable manages
      the slice operator for any subsequent dosage rules:
        - Initialised as "+" (new slice).
        - Set to "=" after dosagefsh is emitted (continue the same slice).
      This ensures `asNeeded` rules are appended to the same dosage slice
      rather than opening a new one.
      `medication.dosagedisplay` provides the human-readable dosage string for
      HTML td 4.

    TD 5 — Reason: `medication.reason.code` conditional; SCT coding.

    narrative: emitHEAD() + emitHTML() both flushed inside text.div.
    CSS class: hl7__ips first25.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                       │ Type     │ Description                                    │
  ├────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                     │ string   │ Resource id for the MedicationStatement.       │
  │ druginstanceid                 │ string   │ Resource id for the Medication (Mode B only).  │
  │ patient.instanceid             │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                  │
  │ patient.name                   │ string   │ Full display name.                             │
  │ medication                     │ object?  │ Empty → Mode A. Non-empty → Mode B.           │
  │   .code.code                   │ string?  │   SNOMED CT code (preferred over RxNorm).      │
  │   .code.display                │ string   │   SNOMED display text.                         │
  │   .code.preferredTerm          │ string?  │   Preferred display override for code.text.    │
  │   .rxnorm.code                 │ string?  │   RxNorm code (used only when SNOMED absent).  │
  │   .rxnorm.display              │ string   │   RxNorm display text.                         │
  │   .start                       │ string?  │   ISO 8601 effectivePeriod start date.         │
  │   .asNeeded                    │ mixed?   │   "true" (string) or CodeableConcept object.   │
  │     .display                   │ string   │     Display when asNeeded is CodeableConcept.  │
  │     .system                    │ string   │     System URI for CodeableConcept.            │
  │     .code                      │ string   │     Code for CodeableConcept.                  │
  │   .dosagefsh                   │ string?  │   Pre-formatted FSH dosage string (AI-gen).    │
  │                                │          │   Injected with \| raw.                        │
  │   .dosagedisplay               │ string?  │   Human-readable dosage for HTML td 4.         │
  │   .reason.code                 │ string?  │   SNOMED code for the clinical reason.         │
  │   .reason.display              │ string   │   Reason display text.                         │
  │ manufacturedDoseForm           │ object?  │   Dose form for Medication.form.coding.        │
  │   .code                        │ string   │   SNOMED CT code.                              │
  │   .display                     │ string   │   Display text (also stored in formdisplay).   │
  │ activeIngredient               │ object?  │   Active ingredient for ingredient[0].         │
  │   .code                        │ string   │   SNOMED CT code.                              │
  │   .display                     │ string   │   Ingredient display text.                     │
  └────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct    — SNOMED CT; medication code, dose form, ingredient, reason,
              "No known medications" (787481004)
    $rxnorm — RxNorm; fallback medication code when SNOMED absent

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-10-21
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

{% if medication is empty %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE A — NO KNOWN MEDICATIONS
  Single MedicationStatement with the SNOMED "no known medications" sentinel.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-MedicationStatement-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicationStatementEuCore
Title: "MedicationStatement"
Description: "MedicationStatement"
Usage: #inline
* id     = "{{ instanceid }}"
* status = #active
{# Fixed SNOMED code for "No known medications (situation)" #}
* medicationCodeableConcept = $sct#787481004 "No known medications (situation)"
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"
{# No dates available — use data-absent-reason extension on effectivePeriod #}
* effectivePeriod.extension.url       = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* effectivePeriod.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{# Single HTML cell — no table structure needed for a sentinel value #}
{{ addHTML_tr() }}
{{ addHTML_td("No known medications") }}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}
{# Narrative — body row only, no HEAD. hl7__ips first25 narrows the first column. #}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips first25">{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

{% else %}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE B — MEDICATION PRESENT
  Instance 1: Medication (MedicationEuCore)
  Instance 2: MedicationStatement (MedicationStatementEuCore)
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

{#
  ── Instance 1: Medication ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The drug product itself. Registered separately so the MedicationStatement
  can reference it by UUID.
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Medication-" ~ druginstanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicationEuCore
Title: "Medication"
Description: "Medication"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ druginstanceid }}"

{#
  Medication coding — mutually exclusive priority:
    SNOMED CT (medication.code.code) is preferred.
    RxNorm is emitted only when SNOMED is absent.
  code.text[=] — sets the preferred term as the text representation of the
    coding context opened by coding[+]. Note: [=] on a non-repeating element
    is unconventional; verify SUSHI output if issues arise.
#}
{% if medication.code.code is not empty %}
* code.coding[+]  = $sct#{{ medication.code.code }} "{{ medication.code.display }}"
{% if medication.code.preferredTerm is not empty %}
* code.text[=]    = "{{ medication.code.preferredTerm }}"
{% endif %}
{% else %}
{# RxNorm fallback — used only when no SNOMED code is available #}
{% if medication.rxnorm.code is not empty %}
* code.coding[+] = $rxnorm#{{ medication.rxnorm.code }} "{{ medication.rxnorm.display }}"
{% endif %}
{% endif %}

{#
  formdisplay — local variable capturing the dose form display string.
  Initialised empty; set to ", <display>" when a dose form is present.
  Reused in text.div (Medication narrative) and HTML td 3 (MedicationStatement).
#}
{% set formdisplay = "" %}
{% if manufacturedDoseForm.code is not empty %}
* form.coding = $sct#{{ manufacturedDoseForm.code }} "{{ manufacturedDoseForm.display }}"
{% set formdisplay = ", " ~ manufacturedDoseForm.display %}
{% endif %}

{# Active ingredient — single ingredient[0] with isActive flag #}
{% if activeIngredient.code is not empty %}
* ingredient[0].itemCodeableConcept = $sct#{{ activeIngredient.code }} "{{ activeIngredient.display }}"
* ingredient[0].isActive            = true
{% endif %}

{# Minimal narrative: preferred term (or display) plus dose form #}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
{{ medication.code.preferredTerm ?? medication.code.display }} {{ formdisplay }}
</div>
"""

{#
  ── Instance 2: MedicationStatement ─────────────────────────────────────────
  Links the patient, the Medication above, the dosage, and the clinical reason.
  Five-column HTML table: Medication | Since | Form | Dosage | Reason
#}
Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-MedicationStatement-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: MedicationStatementEuCore
Title: "MedicationStatement"
Description: "MedicationStatement"
Usage: #inline

{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Medication") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Since") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Form") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Dosage") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reason") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

* id     = "{{ instanceid }}"
* status = #active

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── medicationReference + TD 1: medication name with optional "as needed" ───
  The Reference display string uses the preferred term (or display fallback).

  `medication.asNeeded` handling:
    Case 1 — string "true": appends " - as needed" to the HTML display name.
    Case 2 — CodeableConcept object: appends " - <display>" to the HTML name.
  The `med` local variable accumulates the full display string for HTML td 1.
#}
* medicationReference = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ druginstanceid }}) "{{ medication.code.preferredTerm ?? medication.code.display }}"
{% set med = medication.code.preferredTerm ?? medication.code.display %}
{% if medication.asNeeded is not empty %}
{% if medication.asNeeded == "true" %}
{% set med = med ~ " - as needed" %}
{% endif %}
{% if medication.asNeeded.display is not empty %}
{% set med = med ~ " - " ~ medication.asNeeded.display %}
{% endif %}
{% endif %} {# asNeeded not empty #}
{{ addHTML_td(med) }}

* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{#
  ── TD 2: effective period start ────────────────────────────────────────────
  Start date of the medication course; shows "-" if unknown.
#}
{% if medication.start is not empty %}
* effectivePeriod.start = "{{ medication.start }}"
{{ addHTML_tdnb(medication.start) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 3: dose form ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Populated from `formdisplay` set during the Medication instance above.
  Shows "-" if no dose form was specified.
#}
{% if formdisplay is not empty %}
{{ addHTML_td(formdisplay) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 4: AI-generated dosage + asNeeded FSH rules ─────────────────────────
  `contdose` controls the dosage slice operator:
    "+" → open a new dosage slice (initial state)
    "=" → continue the slice opened by dosagefsh (set after injection)

  `medication.dosagefsh` is raw FSH produced by an AI system — injected
  directly with | raw. After injection, contdose switches to "=" so that
  any subsequent asNeeded rule addresses the same slice.

  `medication.dosagedisplay` provides the human-readable HTML cell value.
#}
{% set contdose = "+" %}
{% if medication.dosagefsh is not empty %}
{{ medication.dosagefsh | raw }}
{% set contdose = "=" %}
{% endif %} {# dosagefsh not empty #}

{# asNeeded FSH rules — emitted on the same dosage slice as dosagefsh #}
{% if medication.asNeeded is not empty %}
{% if medication.asNeeded == "true" %}
* dosage[{{ contdose }}].asNeededBoolean = true
{% endif %}
{% if medication.asNeeded.display is not empty %}
* dosage[{{ contdose }}].asNeededCodeableConcept = {{ medication.asNeeded.system }}#{{ medication.asNeeded.code }} "{{ medication.asNeeded.display }}"
{% endif %}
{% endif %} {# medication.asNeeded not empty #}

{% if medication.dosagedisplay is not empty %}
{{ addHTML_td(medication.dosagedisplay) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %} {# dosagedisplay not empty #}

{#
  ── TD 5: reason ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Clinical reason for the medication; SNOMED CT coding on reasonCode[0].
#}
{% if medication.reason.code is not empty %}
* reasonCode[0].coding = $sct#{{ medication.reason.code }} "{{ medication.reason.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(medication.reason.display) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Both HEAD and HTML bags flushed — full headed table in the narrative.
  CSS class: hl7__ips first25 (first column constrained to ~25% width).
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips first25">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }} {{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

{% endif %} {# medication is empty / not empty #}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
